    "Here, Pr i t 1, refers to the proportion of strategy type i at time t.",
    "This is given by the numerator of the fitness function, Pr i i t S, which is a function f x t i described by the product proportion of strategy type i at time t, Pr i t, by the fitness of i.",
    "The numerator Pr i i t S reflects the sum of all proportions of strategy type i multiplied by the fitness of all strategy types.",
    "The denominator of the fraction j N t Pr j j ¦ 1",
    ", reflects the sum of (total) proportion of all the strategies multiplied by the total payoffs."
  ]
